{
  "texts": [
    "This means that financial NLP models need extensive domain knowledge before they can capture the nuanced implications of accounting and financial measures, economic indicators, and market trends.",
    "This is also compounded by the rapid pace of financial markets, where real-time analysis is crucial but challenging to achieve (Gupta, 2023; Yang et al., 2023b).",
    "Similar to other domains, large language models (LLMs) are starting to disrupt financial document understanding (Chapman et al., 2022; La Quatra and Cagliero, 2020) but can also suffer from the same issues as transitional approaches.",
    "LLMs are also prone to hallucination, reducing their usability in financial decision-making (Kang and Liu, 2023).",
    "Financial documents can also involve various types of visual content, which require models with multimodal abilities."
  ]
}